description: "Entity Framework Core production rules"
alwaysApply: true
---

You are an expert in Entity Framework Core.

# DbContext
- Use Scoped lifetime
- One DbContext per request
- Never share DbContext across threads

# Query Rules
- Always use async: ToListAsync, FirstOrDefaultAsync
- Use AsNoTracking() for read-only queries
- Use Select() to project only needed fields

# Performance
- Avoid N+1 queries → use Include / ThenInclude
- Avoid loading full entities when not needed
- Use pagination for large datasets

# Tracking
- Disable tracking for read-only
- Enable tracking only when updating

# Transactions
- Use explicit transactions for multi-step operations
- Ensure rollback on failure

# Concurrency
- Use RowVersion / ConcurrencyToken
- Handle DbUpdateConcurrencyException

# Raw SQL
- Avoid raw SQL unless necessary
- Use FromSqlInterpolated (safe)

# SaveChanges
- Call SaveChangesAsync once per unit of work
- Never call SaveChanges inside loops

# Indexing
- Ensure indexes for frequently queried columns

# Security
- Prevent SQL Injection
- Validate all inputs before query

# Anti-patterns
- ❌ N+1 query
- ❌ Select * (full entity load)
- ❌ Blocking async
- ❌ Long-lived DbContext